      • setErrorCode

        public void setErrorCode(ResponseCode errorCode)
        Set error code for this message. This method should be called only on messages where the error code is known, Implementations must not require calling this method, because this argument is voluntary in some kinds of message implementations.
        Specified by:
        setErrorCode in interface MessageMapper
        Parameters:
        errorCode - ResponseCode class instance representing the error code number. (e.g. 404 for Not Found)

      • setDiscriminator

        public void setDiscriminator(String discriminator)
        Set disciminator of this message. Discriminator is the full class name of the Message object implementation and it must be possible to instantiate the message implementing object by use of java reflection feature.
        Specified by:
        setDiscriminator in interface MessageMapper
        Parameters:
        discriminator - String of fully represented class name of the specific implementation of the Message; it is created by calling Class.getName() method of the specific message implementation
